# Global Claude Instructions (Windows)

## Windows bash freeze workaround

Always output at least one line of text before making any Bash tool call.
This prevents a UI race condition where the terminal window freezes when bash
is the first operation in a response.

## PowerShell syntax

Use PowerShell-native syntax in all Bash tool calls. This means:
- Use `$null` instead of `/dev/null`
- Use backslashes in Windows paths (e.g. `C:\Users\...`)
- Use PowerShell cmdlets (Get-ChildItem, Get-Content, Select-String, etc.) instead of Unix equivalents
- Use semicolons or pipeline operators, not `&&` to chain commands
- Use `Remove-Item` instead of `rm`, `Copy-Item` instead of `cp`, etc.
- Use `$env:VAR` instead of `$VAR` for environment variables
